Implementing a while loop in Actian 4GL OpenROAD While Statement involves several steps:

1. Define a condition to be met by the loop.
2. Set a variable to hold the value of the condition.
3. Use a "while" statement to specify that the block of code should be executed as long as the condition is true.

Here's an example:
```
condition = TRUE;
variable = 0;

while condition do
    /* Code to execute */
    print variable;
    variable = variable + 1;
endwhile;
```
This code will continue to execute until the condition becomes false, at which point it will stop.

